result.name: Tim Ho Wan

reviews.text: Dumplings, steam rolls, deep fried stuff. Funky stuff like pork liver and chicken feet. Great for food sharing. Tasty. In-restaurant experience not the greatest, waiters are not very helpful, kind of pushy and transactional. Though that may also just be the local style. I don't have that much reference.

Love the food here. Of all their outlets we prefer going to the one at Olympic, not for anything else but for the space they have. Other outlets have smaller spaces which makes it a little difficult with small children. The wait time varies depending on what time you go. But we have not had to wait for more than 15 minutes even on a busy day. Recommended items are the BBQ pork buns, egg white and shrimp spring rolls, char Sui pork vermicelli, spare ribs in black bean sauce and pork and shrimp dumplings in chui chow style.

Love the place, the dishes are really good and at affordable prices.
We ended up ordering almost every dish on the menu and liked them all.
The place is crowded with people and that is part of the magic this place has to offer.
Dont come with expectations of a high end fancy restaurant, its simple and good, you wont regret visiting there.
And dont forget to come hungry because you will be eating a lot.

Had a great dining experience here. Tim Ho Wan has gone huge and global these days. Miss the good old days where you have to wait in line for an hour outside on the alley because they had this cramped dining space. Still great food, though.
Food taste good and fast serving. Clean restaurant and bright though tables are a little busy when all the food comes in a shot. The roasted pork sweet bun is a must order.

reviews.text: The mall is spacious and clean. It is very comfortable to walk around. People can have lunch or dinner in the mall as a lot of restaurants and fast food shops are available there.
A popular mall at Olympic station for local . Many mid- level shops in Phase 1 to  phase 3 Plaza. Easy to spend a few hours here.
Decent shopping variety.  More to local families. And has 3 different buildings.
A modern shopping mall with a fantastic food court. Close to the MTR,  bus and taxi stands.

A large shopping mall with a few phases joined together. The direction is not too clear hence makes it harder to find shops if you are new to the place. Overall the mall is clean and comfortable to shop. Linked with the mtr station so getting there is easy.

reviews.text: 道地的就是好吃😋我在台灣到底為什麼要花冤枉錢😂😂😂
ミシュラン一つ星の有名店。場所が分かりにくい。ショッピングモール内からのアクセスはより分かりにくい。外から回り込んだ方が良い。２名だと相席が基本か。メニューが分かり憎く、英語表記も写真も無い。WEB サイトで画像と料理名を確認した。料理はさすがに旨い。日本では行列の店。本場香港でしかも場所的に穴場店だと思う。

Dumplings, steam rolls, deep fried stuff. Funky stuff like pork liver and chicken feet. Great for food sharing. Tasty. In-restaurant experience not the greatest, waiters are not very helpful, kind of pushy and transactional. Though that may also just be the local style. I don't have that much reference.

Love the food here. Of all their outlets we prefer going to the one at Olympic, not for anything else but for the space they have. Other outlets have smaller spaces which makes it a little difficult with small children. The wait time varies depending on what time you go. But we have not had to wait for more than 15 minutes even on a busy day. Recommended items are the BBQ pork buns, egg white and shrimp spring rolls, char Sui pork vermicelli, spare ribs in black bean sauce and pork and shrimp dumplings in chui chow style.

世界一安いミシュランひとつ星獲得店ということで行ってきました。朝9時頃でしたが、超満席でした。
言葉がわからないので、ネットでランキングを調べて頼んでみました。
鶏の爪？と鶏肉が乗っている丼が美味しかったです‼朝からお腹いっぱい食べて1人1500円くらいでした。1500円でミシュラン獲得店の味を堪能出来たので大満足です。
